review_blob: New Belgium hasnt impressed me since its arrival to PA, but this one is damn good. It says Tangerine IPA and it follows through on that promise. Juicy and easy drinking.
Velvety smooth, chocolate abound in both aroma and flavor. Would like it to be boozier, but it still works.
Decent white IPA. Definitely pick out the wheat malt base and it has a moderately bitter citrus hop presence.

I feel like a bit of dick for saying this, but I starting to think Three Floyds is overrated, a big hype machine that churns out of bunch of mediocre beers, but their reputation is buoyed by some of their great beers (Dreadnaught, Zombie Dust). This one is simply meh.
Cant believe this is rated so low. Its a pale ale with blood orange and tastes and smells like what it should. I liked it.
beer_name: Great South Bay Tasting Room Exclusive #06: Robert Moses Blood Orange Pale Ale

review_blob: Signature Ommegang, always doing their due process in regards to Belgian styles. Nice carbonation, esters, rye spice notes.
beer_name: Ommegang Scythe and Sickle Harvest Ale

review_blob: This isnt any good. In fact its shitty. Where are the aromatic hops? Wheres the malt? It tastes like stale, creamy cardboard.
Its a blonde, so nothing stands out, but overall its decent for what it is. Crisp, drinkability, subtle malt sweetness and hops.
Such an interesting brew and so complex, that I wasnt sure all the flavors would work together, but they do. Coffee, chocolate, caramel, resin, pine, and citrus. Wow.

Reminds me so much of Eternal Sunshine by Pizza Boy, which makes sense since Terry Hawbaker, Pizza Boys brewer, owns Intangible Ale, the collab partner of Evil Twin on this. Acidic citrus, namely lemon, with a light and refreshing malt profile. Dig it.
beer_name: Evil Twin / Intangible Ales Sour Bikini

review_blob: Golden pour with great clarity and semi-creamy white head and plenty of lacing. Its well balanced, but nothing stands out. Floral nose with orange in both aroma and flavor, a bit soapy.
Wow, thats good. Creamy cocoa colored head with black pour. Coffee, chocolate, roasted malts, and mild bitterness. Medium bodied. The lager version of a robust porter.
Cloudy brown with khaki colored head. Dark fruit, caramel, coffee, Belgian yeast and sugar, toasted malts. Very complex, but the flavor isnt anything amazing.

Damn, Clown Shoes brings every day, all day. It tastes exactly like it says - coffee with subtle nuttiness and spice notes. My only complaint, would have liked a semi-creamy head, but it was pretty much nonexistent.
beer_name: Clown Shoes Coffee Pecan Pie Porter

review_blob: This is harsh. I wanted to like it, but no. Very bitter, hop mixture doesnt work for my palate, and the malt backbone is where? The entire thing is muddled.
beer_name: Evil Genius Chickity China the Chinese Chicken

review_blob: I was very excited for this beer. Its probably exactly what Yuengling was aiming for - a moderately hopped lager that would appeal to their typical clientele. It leaves the craft beer seeker feeling flat though. Too much lager flavor, not enough hops (the IP!). Its okay, especially for the price, but nothing worth seeking out...unfortunately.
Exactly what it says it is- barley wine at the heart with a nice brandy/oak finish. Woody, booze, sweet malts, old hop bitterness. Nice beer.
Damn, so much spice. Too much spice? Certainly is a Christmas inspired ale. Belgian yeast comes through, sweetness of the malts and possibly Belgian candied sugar.
beer_name: Fegleys Brew Works Rude Elfs Reserve

review_blob: Looks like a hazy orange juice. Big nectarine aromas and flavor. Pleasantly puckering. Really enjoyed it.
beer_name: Jacks Abby Sour Barrel Project: Nectarine Sour

review_blob: Very good pale ale...albeit on the darker side. The hops bring an array of aromas - pine, floral, pith/zest, and spice. Really dig this.
Quite possibly the best golden ale Ive ever had. Belgian yeast notes, wheat, orange peel, clove, tongue tingle, citrusy hops, soft carbonation. Evolution should be proud of this beer.
Im not sure there is a better cheap-ass beer on the market today. Crisp, clean, slightly sweet, subdued bitterness, refreshing. Good for what it is.
Gose has become one of my favorite styles. The depth of flavors in such a low ABV brew makes me happy inside. Tart, salty, citrusy, minerally, yeasty, yummy!
beer_name: Destihl Wild Sour Series: Here Gose Nothin

review_blob: Nice pils, which hits all the right notes - crisp, clean, soft carbonation, enough noble hop bitterness to be noticeable, but no intrusive or abusive. Decent.

Trillium always kills it. No mediocre or merely drinkable with them, only crushable. Orangish pour with huge fluffy head (a bit over carbed), citra galore in the nose and flavor along with that signature saison yeast funk. Nice.
Hey everybody, its autumn, time to brew a pumpkin ale. Why do I even bother with this style? I dont hate it, but its always just meh.
Pleasantly surprised with the crispness of this pale ale. Nice malts along with assertive enough hop profile. Totally crushable.
beer_name: Spider Bite First Bite Pale Ale

review_blob: A depth of flavors going on here - moleasses, chocolate, bourbon, oak, booze, coffee. So malty, so complex, so strong. Dig it.
beer_name: Jackie Os Bourbon Barrel Dark Apparition

review_blob: Blah, blah, blah...another pumpkin ale. This one isnt terrible, but its much the same as all the others. Whatever.

Before ever reading this beers deScription, I was like "does this have lavender in chamomile in it?" I was half right. Perhaps the hops are giving it an extra floral aroma. Either way, its a nice spin put onto a simple style. Dark Horse always having fun with their brews.
Straw yellow with frothy white head. Cucumber, cantaloupe, and grass in aroma and flavor. I HATE cucumber, but this beers taste is unique and refreshing.

I like the fact that the base beer is still evident in aroma in flavor and that barrel aging only added character to it, rather than mask its integrity. Spices, oak, bourbon/booze, and pumpkin for the win!
A burnt sienna color pour with semi-creamy lasting head. Aroma of dark cherries and the flavor follows. Tastes like a Belgian brown ale with subtly tart cherries.

Pumpkin beers arent my thing, but I appreciate the nuances of this one compared to the masses. The honey smooths out the palate, rendering the spices not as biting or potent. Subtle pumpkin flavor along with allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg. Some caramel sweetness from the malt bill and even a bit of bittering hops for that West Coast flare.
Wanted to like this more than I did, but its just too sweet and too much vanilla. Not terrible, just mediocre. Little thin, smell is meh.

I applaud the idea of a pumpkin saison and to an extent I enjoy the change of pace from other pumpkin ales. Soft carbonation, spices play in accordance with the saison yeast, but overall I find the saison style a bit lacking in this beer. Would have liked more of the farmhouse funk to come through.
A very well balanced red ale considering Sam Adams took a hoppy angle. Roasted caramel malts, pine and spice from the hops. Decent.
I prefer a Oktoberfest of this style moreso than others because it has minimal sweetness and a nice bitterness with that lager crispness.
UPDATED: NOV 3, 2015

Yeah, Trillium is awesome. Looks like a super hazed wheat ale, bright yellow but cloudy like pineapple juice...smells like it to. A nice sharp hop bite upfront followed by lovely tropical fruitiness. Yum.
Bright hazy yellow-orange, like a sunrise. Think head with minimal lacing. Wheat and pils-esque malt bill, but the hops are the showcase here. Pine and grapefruit pith. Lasting bitterness.
Copper colored pour. That unmistakable Oktoberfest sweetness. Not my favorite style by any stretch, but a good representation nonetheless.

Slightly hazy light orange with to bright yellow appearance with thin white head and lacing. Big juicy hops along with pine. Based on the aroma I would have thought it to be a bit sweeter and chewy, but still very good.
beer_name: Trillium Sleeper Street IPA - Double Dry Hopped

review_blob: Thats some serious roasted malts flavor. Mostly bitter coffee flavor with a very smooth mouthfeel. Otter Creek is good, almost always.
Golden pour with thin head, tight bubbles, and lacing. Aromas and flavors of pine, fresh cut grass, sweet malts, and tropical fruits. Extremely well balanced for an IPA. Pretty impressed.
Nice take on the Oktoberfest style. Crisp, just right amount of sweetness and hop bitterness. Very good lager.
Golden pour with nearly nonexistent head, in fact, the carbonation is too low in this. Smells of musty malts, floral hops, and sweet corn. Not very good.
Utterly awful. Metallic flavors, unlikable earthiness, bitter with lacking malts. Bad.
beer_name: Saucony Creek Stonefly India Pale Ale

review_blob: Straw color with thin, lasting head and lacing. Looks and tastes slightly better than a typical macro lager. Subtle floral hops with hay/wheat flavor. Easy drinking, crisp, but nothing special.
